name: ECUA
comments: Electronic Control Unit Accupack. Controls AIRs. Measures accupack voltages, currents and measures BMS
v5 Voltages message is sent for CCU compatibility.

items.name: pendingChargerDetect
items.description: Awaiting detection of car or charger

items.name: ready
items.description: Awaiting SDC completion to begin precharge

items.name: waitingForVdiff
items.description: Precharge part 2: wait for ΔV to approach zero

items.name: fatalError
items.description: A fatal error occured and the AMS is latched

items.name: cooldown
items.description: Precharge failed, cooling down before retrying

items.name: hvmCooldown
items.description: HV- failed to close, cooling down before retrying

messages.name: Status
comments: Base status of ECUA and its subsystems (AMS)

fields.name: SDC_HV_ILOCK
comments: True if HV interlock is closed

fields.name: SDC_IMD
comments: True if SDC is not broken by IMD

fields.name: SDC_OUT
comments: SDC out to final stretch (BSPD etc...)

fields.name: LATCH_SDC_AMS
comments: HW latch engaged (caused by IMD or AMS)

messages.name: Limits
comments: ACP power limits that are calculated in time based on temperature and votlages.
For example if undervoltage the PWR_OUT should be some few kW value to let the driver decide to risk.
If ACP is full PWR_IN should be 0.

fields.name: Curr_HV_out
comments: HV Current (positive if energy flowing outwards)

messages.name: AMSVolts
comments: AMS message for voltages. Uses multiplexors for identifications of dataset. AMS measures all stacks in the same time but sent that in specific order determined by muxing.

fields.name: StackID
comments: Index of stack in ACP - mx

fields.name: SetID
comments: Index of parallel cell group measurement  in stack - mx

fields.name: Volt
comments: Voltages of cell sets in parralel

messages.name: AMSTemp
comments: AMS message for temperatures. Uses multiplexors for identification of dataset.

fields.name: StackID
comments: Index of stack in ACP - mx

fields.name: SetID
comments: Index of measurement in stack - mx

fields.name: StackID
comments: Index of stack in ACP - multiplexed

items.name: HVM_MELT
items.description: HV- closed even though it shouldn't be

items.name: HVP_MELT
items.description: HV+ closed even though it shouldn't be

items.name: VDIFF_TIMEOUT
items.description: precharge failed to equaize AIRs x Accu voltage

items.name: BMS_CELL_MIN_VOLTAGE
items.description: Voltage of a cell is too low

items.name: BMS_CELL_BALANCE
items.description: Imbalance between some cells is too high

items.name: BMS_COMMUNICATION
items.description: BMS communication error - probably not connected

items.name: TOO_MANY_ERRORS
items.description: Too many non-fatal errors => escalated to a fatal error

name: CCU
comments: Charger Control Unit, compatible with FSE.04x and newer.

messages.name: ChargerHeartbeat
comments: Hotfix for a missing interlock. Sent by ECUA to CCU.

fields.name: ready
comments: 1 of AIRs are closed correctly, zero otherwise

messages.name: Announce
comments: Hotfix for missing hard-wired charger detection.

name: ECUB
comments: Distribution of power, manages low voltage battery and car status manager.

items.name: NOT_READY
items.description: SDC interrupted -> not ready for start

items.name: PRECHARGE
items.description: ACP is being precharged -> waiting for ECUA status

enum_types.name: Notready_reason
enum_types.description: Describes latest error which caused NOT_READY Carstate.

items.description: Vehicle was latched at the startup

items.description: Vehicle was latched due to BSPD error

items.name: LATCH_AMS
items.description: Vehicle was latched due to AMS error

name: VDCU
comments: Vehicle dynamics control unit. Model based design using Simulink and C2000 TI DSP MCU. Commanding motors when CarState is STARTED. Using different strategies for different sensor failure or limitations. Only this unit commands MCU's.

messages.name: Param
comments: Parameters changed in ECUS are muxed and sent after every change. Acknowledge is expected in next 20ms. If not acknowledged parameters are resend unitl 5th time. Whole parameters are boadcasted in a loop. The acknowledges parameters data are then displayed.

fields.name: SEQ_PARAM
comments: Up counter for every corresponding parameter change

fields.name: load
comments: Measured wheel load at scales on water level surface

messages.name: Controller
comments: Overal actual values of motor torques

messages.name: WheelFz
comments: Calculated and calibrated wheel loads. Using accelerometer, configuration and suspension displacement sensors

messages.name: Param_ACK
comments: ECUS is displaying and evaluating the parameters that are only sent and acknowledged. That means that the initial parameter set is sent from ECUS and should be acknowledged of the actual used values by unit

fields.name: SEQ_Param
comments: Up counter for every corresponding parameter change acknowledgement

name: ECUF
comments: ECU-Front distributes power to another ECUs situated in the front of the car. The unit also operates car's dashboard, checks the state of SDC and provides steering wheel angle, front brake temperature and suspension displacement.
